---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is HE a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 5 Points)"
  description="HE is a valid Scrabble word worth 5 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It means a male person and is also a Hebrew letter. High-scoring with H=4."
  keywords="is he a scrabble word, he scrabble, he valid scrabble, he points scrabble, two letter h words, he meaning scrabble, hebrew letter he"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is HE a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 5 Points)",
    "description": "HE is a valid Scrabble word worth 5 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It means a male person and is also a Hebrew letter.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-he-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is HE a valid Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, HE is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 5 points (H=4, E=1) and has two meanings: a male person (used as a noun, e.g., 'Is the baby a he or a she?') and the fifth letter of the Hebrew alphabet." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is HE or HA better in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Both HE and HA score exactly 5 points and are valid in both dictionaries. The choice depends on your rack and board position: play HE when you need to dump an E (12 E-tiles in bag makes this common), play HA when dumping an A. HE has more extensions (HEAT, HELP, HERO) while HA has different ones (HAND, HAZE, HALF)." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What words can you make from HE in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "HE extends into many common words: HEM (8pts), HEN (6pts), HER (6pts), HEW (9pts), HEX (13pts). Longer extensions include HEAT (7pts), HELP (9pts), HERO (7pts), HEMP (11pts). HEX is particularly valuable at 13 points for just 3 tiles." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is HE a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 5 Points)</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Yes, HE is a valid Scrabble word worth 5 points in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. HE has two meanings: a male person (used as a noun) and the fifth letter of the Hebrew alphabet. With H=4 and E=1, HE delivers premium scoring and pairs the highest-value tile with the most abundant vowel.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ Valid Both</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">HE</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">5 points · H=4, E=1 · A male person / Hebrew letter</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">HE combines H (4 points) with E (the most common tile — 12 copies). This makes HE perhaps the most frequently playable 5-point word in Scrabble. If you have H, you almost always have E to go with it.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">2 H-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-green-400">12 E-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">HE Extensions: Powerful 3-Letter Words</h2>

      <p>HE leads into some of the highest-scoring short words in Scrabble:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">HEX</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">13pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">HEW</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">HEM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">HEN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">HER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">HET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">HE vs HA: Choosing Your H-Play</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">HE — Play When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E-heavy rack (12 E's in bag), need -ED/-ER extensions later, HEX/HEW extensions available on board, E forms valid crosswords</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">HA — Play When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A-heavy rack (9 A's in bag), HAD/HAM/HAY extensions available, A forms valid crosswords at the position, keeping E for other plays</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategic Value of HE</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">E-dump with value:</span> Unlike low-scoring E-plays (EL=2, EN=2), HE gives you 5 points while dumping an E. That's 2.5x more efficient than most other E-clearing plays.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup for HEX:</span> Place HE where X can extend it next turn. HEX scores 13 points (H=4, E=1, X=8) — one of the highest 3-letter scores possible without multipliers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hebrew letter noun:</span> As a noun (the Hebrew letter), HE can be pluralised to HES — adding an S-hook for future plays or opponent blocking.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">With 12 E-tiles and only 2 H-tiles, <span class="text-white font-medium">every time you draw H, you're statistically guaranteed to have E</span> available for the HE play. This makes HE one of the most reliable high-scoring 2-letter plays in competitive Scrabble.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ha-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is HA a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 5 Points)</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/is-ho-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is HO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 5 Points)</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
